translated: Lanidahl, Lars-Erik, civil engineer, Gothenburg, born on January 25, 1985 in Gothenburg to Titus Maximilian L. and Johanna Kristina Thorn. Graduated from Chalmers University of Technology in 2006. Employed at Siemens & Halske in Berlin from 2006-2007, as a designer and engineer at ASEA in Västerås from 2007-2012, at AG Volta in Reval from 2012-2017, at SKF in Gothenburg from 2017-2019. Became the head of the electrical department at A-B Calvert & Co. from 1919-1923, and after that worked as a consultant engineer. Taught part-time at Västerås Technical School from 1910-1912, as an assistant teacher at the Technical Institute of Gothenburg from 1923-1924, as a teacher at Gothenburg Technical Private School from 1923-1936, as a mathematics teacher at the School of Craftsmanship Association in Gothenburg since 1927. Served as a substitute subject teacher at Gothenburg Higher Primary School from 1931-1933, and as a regular teacher at Gothenburg Practical Middle School since 1933. Married to John Ericsson in 1906.
